description: Heyri Art Village is a cultural village where Korean writers, filmmakers, architects, musicians and other artists from various fields gather. In this community, in addition to ordinary homes, there are also workshops, art galleries, museums, etc. for literary and art workers, forming a complex space for creation, display, and communication. So far, there are more than 40 art buildings in Heyri Art Village, including museums, exhibition halls, concert halls, bookstores, etc. It is expected that this number will increase by about 10 times in 3-4 years. In addition, there are more than 10 cafes and restaurants in the Art Valley.
